cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "meshtastic-security-audit: Passive security audit toolkit for Meshtastic packet captures"
message: "If you use this toolkit, please cite it as below."
type: software
authors:
  - given-names: "Ali Murtaza"
    family-names: "Bhutto"
    orcid: "https://orcid.org/0009-0007-2787-943X"
license: MIT
repository-code: "https://github.com/thunderstornX/meshtastic-security-audit"
keywords:
  - Meshtastic
  - LoRa
  - mesh networking
  - security audit
  - packet analysis
  - encryption
  - LPWAN
abstract: >
  meshtastic-security-audit is a Python toolkit that passively analyses
  Meshtastic packet captures (PCAP) and surfaces four classes of
  misconfiguration and information disclosure: use of the well-known
  default channel key, node-identifier enumeration exposure across the
  observed mesh, unencrypted traffic on supposedly encrypted channels,
  and GPS coordinate leakage in position payloads. The toolkit ships a
  Scapy-based parser for the Meshtastic frame structure on the LoRa
  link layer, four independent detectors, an HTML and JSON reporter,
  and a Click-based CLI. Synthetic Scapy-crafted packet fixtures
  underpin the test suite so no live RF capture is required for CI.
